    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/11a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Australia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 23, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. American papers have carried an Associated Press story with a Sydney date
                    line of October 20 stating that according to reports from Canberra negotiations
                    have been completed between the United States, Great Britain, China, the
                    Netherlands East Indies, New Zealand, and Australia for a united Pacific
                    front.</p>
                <p>There is no definite indication that Australia’s agreement on the matter of
                    Pacific air bases was the occasion for this story. The fact however that the
                    story was apparently given out the day after the Australian Government had
                    expressed its concurrence in our proposal has given us some slight concern here.
                    Will you, in your discretion, call attention to this and emphasize the
                    desirability of keeping the matter of air bases strictly confidential.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
